<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:large;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>odysseyseq@yahoo.com</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
Please DO NOT post an application in this forum.  <br>
Thank you,<br>
Minz<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:helvetica;font-size:medium;">REQUIRMENTS</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:large;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Odysseys is always open for recruitment</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> although at this moment we are recruiting very few new people. Please read the guide lines below if you are interested in becoming a member of Odysseys. Some people will be allowed to apply w/o all requirements, but no guildtag will be given until all requirements are met.<br>
<br>
*Attendance - This is the single most important thing in joining Odysseys. If you are not able to put in the required play time, this isnt the guild for you. Our total guild roster atm is about 90. People thinking of joining and then Disappearing need not apply, you will be removed from guild. AFKing excessively on raids will also result in your removal. Raid start times will vary, but they will be posted a week in advance for people to make the necessary plans. Regardless plan on Raiding 5 days a week on average 5-6 hours a day.<br>
Raid times will vary from 6pm EST at the earliest on up to 4am EST on rare occasions. Most Raids should be between 7pm EST to 2am EST<br>
Applicants must maintain a 60% attendance average.<br>
<br>
*Level - NO EXCEPTIONS, if your not 65 and would like to join, use the time it takes you to level up and get to know our members. We may accept applications from people below 65 but you will not be guildtagged until you reach level 65<br>
<br>
*AA Skills - A minimum of 50aa is also required with very few exceptions. 50 is not alot of AA especially since we have members with over 400. We also expect you to continue leveling your AAs after joining. Please Note some classes will be an exception to this, but are still required to continue leveling AAs after joining<br>
<br>
*FLAGS - Must have prior to applying :<br>
<br>
Plane of Valor (Aerin Dar)<br>
Plane of Storms<br>
Bastion of Thunder<br>
Plane of Nightmares (Hedge Walk &amp; Terris Thule)<br>
Plane of Disease (Grummus)<br>
Plane of Tactics (Behemoth)<br>
<br>
<br>
*No changed Primary characters after you join. You were recruited as that class for a reason. If you are able to 2 box both at raid level and the alt meets all raid requirements, officers may allow it.<br>
<br>
*Language - We are like most guilds, we have some fun, foul language and mature discussion material is not unusual. Be prepared for it, this isnt sunday school<br>
<br>
*Gear - You are required to have a way to invis yourself, an EB item, A way to shrink yourself and an indoor useable right click item.<br>
In addition you are required to be able to get all Resists to 120 without buffs.<br>
<br>
We will be adamant that you follow our rules.<br>
We require people who dont mind dying alot to learn a new encounter.<br>
We require people who dont mind evercamping for boring quests for keys and items that will help us advance.<br>
We require people who play alot and want to win and help each other.<br>
We require people that want to have fun and not log in to simply collect Merit and loots<br>
We require people who play their class with a high level of skill and know their classes abilities inside and out <br>
We require people who want to move ahead and progress in game<br>
We require people who can be anywhere in the game within 15 mins of a raid being called, and not require directions<br>
We require people to be positive thinking and optimistic<br>
We require people to have their Epics, or to be over them, we will not raid to finish your Epics<br>
We operate on a Merit System.<br>
This means we try to base loot on contribution.<br>
You will most likely not get loot fast in Odysseys, if you are here for fast loot, then go elsewhere.<br>
It will most likely be 2 months before you acrue enough Merit to start recieving quality items. You will however have fun and see the highest end content that Everquest has to offer. If you are patient and persistent and contribute then you will get the Phat Lewt :P<br>
We Require Disciplined players. If you have A.D.D., and are off your meds or Turets syndrome then take it down the road, we are not an equal opportunity employer. We require people to pay attention and follow orders at raids <br>
<br>
